    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: Single-page vertical layout with clear thematic sections: 1) Hero/Title, 2) Interactive Itinerary, 3) Time Allocation Chart, 4) Vehicle/Pricing, 5) Inclusions/Exclusions, 6) Booking CTA. Interactions: Itinerary (Click-to-expand list items to show stop details), Pricing (Tabs/buttons to select vehicle type, which dynamically updates the price display), Chart (Hover-to-see tooltips on the time allocation chart). User Flow: User lands, sees the package title. Scrolls to the itinerary, clicks stops they're interested in. Views the chart to understand time commitments. Checks pricing for their group size (vehicle type). Sees inclusions/exclusions. Clicks "Book Now." Why this structure: This mirrors a user's natural "shopping" process for a tour package: What is it? What do I see? How long does it take? How much does it cost? What's included? How do I buy? It's task-oriented and logical. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: [Report Info: Day-wise itinerary -> Goal: Organize & Inform -> Viz/Presentation: Interactive vertical list -> Interaction: On-click reveals details (description, time) for each stop -> Justification: More engaging and less overwhelming than a static text block -> Library/Method: Vanilla JS, HTML, Tailwind], [Report Info: List of locations and suggested timings -> Goal: Compare -> Viz/Presentation: Horizontal Bar Chart -> Interaction: Tooltips on hover -> Justification: Visually represents which stops take the most time -> Library/Method: Chart.js (Canvas)], [Report Info: Vehicle types and corresponding prices -> Goal: Compare & Inform -> Viz/Presentation: Interactive pricing cards with tabs for vehicle selection -> Interaction: Clicking a vehicle type updates the displayed price -> Justification: Allows users to easily see pricing for their specific need -> Library/Method: Vanilla JS, HTML, Tailwind] -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            background-color: #FDFBF8;
